column5: 1. How much were you able to control events?
column6: 2. How responsive was the environment to actions that you initiated (or performed)?
column7: 3. How natural did your interactions with the environment seem?
column8: 4. How much did the visual aspects of the environment involve you?
column9: 5. How natural was the mechanism which controlled movement through the environment?
column10: 6. How compelling was your sense of objects moving through space?
column11: 7. How much did your experiences in the virtual environment seem consistent with your real-world experiences?
column12: 8. Were you able to anticipate what would happen next in response to the actions that you performed?
column13: 9. How completely were you able to actively survey or search the environment using vision?
column14: 10. How compelling was your sense of moving around inside the virtual environment?
column15: 11. How closely were you able to examine objects?
column16: 12. How well could you examine objects from multiple viewpoints?
column17: 13. How involved were you in the virtual environment experience?
column18: 14. How much delay did you experience between your actions and expected outcomes?
column19: 15. How quickly did you adjust to the virtual environment experience?
column20: 16. How proficient in moving and interacting with the virtual environment did you feel at the end of the experience?
column21: 17. How much did the visual display quality interfere or distract you from performing assigned tasks or required activities?
column22: 18. How much did the control devices interfere with the performance of assigned tasks or with other activities?
column23: 19. How well could you concentrate on the assigned tasks or required activities rather than on the mechanisms used to perform those tasks or activities?
column24: 20. How much did the auditory aspects of the environment involve you?
column25: 21. How well could you identify sounds?
column26: 22. How well could you localize sounds?
column27: 23. How well could you actively survey or search the virtual environment using touch?
column28: 24. How well could you move or manipulate objects in the virtual environment?
